general.risk_assessment: Low Risk: Strong fundamentals, worth long-term holding
general.desc: iFAST Corp Ltd is an investment holding company. It is engaged in the development of software, marketing of unit trusts, exchange-traded funds, listed stocks, debt securities, and Singapore government securities through websites and acting as an investment advisor, dealer, and custodian in the securities. The company operates through geographic segments are Singapore, Hong Kong, Malaysia, the United Kingdom, and China. The Singapore region generates maximum revenue for the company. iFAST receives revenue in the form of commissions and fees.
general.short_desc: iFAST Corp Ltd together with its subsidiaries provides internet-based investment products distribution platform. The company provides investment products and services to financial advisory firms, financial institutions, banks, multinational companies.

zscore.name: Altman Z-Score
zscore.details: Altman Z-score of 1.95 is in the grey area. This implies that the company is under some kind of financial stress. If it is below 1.8, the company may face bankruptcy risk.

Long-Term Debt.name: Long-Term Debt
Long-Term Debt.details: iFAST Corp Ltd keeps issuing new debt. Over the past 3 years, it issued SGD 111.796 million of debt.

Total Assets.name: Asset Growth
Total Assets.details: If a company builds assets at 36.1% a year, faster than its revenue growth rate of 13.2% over the past 5 years, it means that the company may be getting less efficient.

roic_vs_wacc.name: ROIC vs WACC
roic_vs_wacc.details: Company's return on invested capital is less than the weighted average cost of capital. It might not be capital efficient
